I'm Patrick Mueller, the artistic director of Control Group Productions – a dance-based intermedia performance company based in Colorado.We've been building the Front Range performance scene since 2009 with innovation-driven, entirely singular new works and a broad-platform community development vision. We're in a wonderful moment RIGHT NOW where this vision is beginning to translate into long-term, sustainable growth. We need your help to take this strong step forward. We hope you'll get behind this awesome moment in our organization's development. Your donation will fuel an extraordinary season of company work, outreach programs in local high schools, and curation and support of other local companies. Every little bit counts, and meeting our goal (or exceeding it!) means the ability not only to capitalize on our planned season, but also to take on new opportunities as they arise and to continue our momentum into 2017-18 and beyond. OUR 2016-17 SEASONAug. 18-27: WHOLENESS (dances made to be viewed in the dark, creation #2) in the Galleria at Denver Performing Arts ComplexSept. 3-4: Home:2016 – a mini-festival of works from our Artist Services programSept. 12-Dec. 20: Dynamic World-Making program at Jefferson County Open SchoolOct. 22-Nov. 12: ALONE WITH TODD (dances made to be viewed in the dark, creation #3) at Colorado Conservatory of Dance (Broomfield), Boulder Creative Collective, and Buntport Theater (Denver)Nov. 18-20: Premiere of commissioned new work with Open Dance Project, Houston, TXJan. 2017: XX by Lauren Beale, Ondine Geary, Brooke McNamara, and Kate Speer (an Artist Services program co-presentation)Jan-May 2017: Dynamic World-Making at another school in Jefferson CountyApr/May 2017: AGGREGATE IMMATERIALITY (dances made to be viewed in the dark, creation #4) in Denver, Boulder, & BroomfieldAug. 2017: controlled encounters with mobile architecture – a site-specific work for transit centers in Denver, Boulder, & Broomfield HOW WE'RE MAKING IT HAPPENWe've been building toward this moment of growth for 2 years. We've laid in infrastructure and strategic partnerships, new capacities and funding sources, and a whole lot of potent vision for stunning art and powerful new programming. Over the last year we've:
entered SCFD's Tier III;
stepped up our grant writing and built relationships with grantors;
solidified resource-sharing relationships that magnify our reach and impact;
commenced a new works series – dances made to be viewed in the dark – with 7 major projects currently planned;
initiated a new Community Engagement program at high schools in Jefferson County;
acquired valuable new equipment for design and production;
professionalized our board and administrative operations.
Now we're ready to dive in. In the last 3 months we brought in $14K in foundation and civic grants, and another $5K from a dozen generous individuals who believe deeply in what we do and wanted to seed our fall fundraising effort.This Indiegogo campaign will get us the rest of the way to a solid budget for this huge season.Our campaign is reaching out to all of us who love the art, and who struggle to bring more of it into our world. It's a call to our friends and colleagues, to working artists and creative businesses, to our die-hard fans and to the folks who've been looking for extraordinary, innovation-driven aesthetic experiences in Colorado and finally figured out where to look.We're not asking for angel donors or 4-digit philanthropists in this campaign (although, of course and by all means, please donate at that level if you're so moved!). This is a call for a whole community to get behind what we're doing, in $10s and $20s and $50 increments (maybe a couple Benjamins too!), so that we can serve that community deeply and fully.We're asking our grassroots to dig down. We're asking for your pocket change, a couple drinks or a new shirt's worth of support. We're asking you to bring whatever you can to the table, to get behind us as we advance the Colorado arts scene with innovation and vision from a community of extraordinary artists. We hope you'll support us.
